<F P=102>   AU1804104594 Prague CTK in English 1747 GMT 16 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1804104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 16 (CTK) -- The People's Union of 
National and Social Salvation (LUNSZ) led by former high-ranking 
Communist Party official Miroslav Stepan, today condemned "NATO 
aggressive air strikes and other interference in Yugoslavia" in 
a statement given to CTK. 
  The LUNSZ favors the peaceful settlement and ending of 
hostilities in Yugoslavia without external interference, says 
the statement. "NATO has no right whatsoever to interfere in the 
former Yugoslavia and through its military actions there has 
again confirmed its aggressive nature," it adds. 
  "The experience with NATO's illegal actions in ex-Yugoslavia 
confirms the truth of all citizens and organizations which 
oppose the Czech Republic's joining NATO which could draw it 
into fratricidal wars for foreign interests," LUNSZ members 
assert. 
  The statement says that the LUNSZ supports the position of 
Russia which demands that the war conflict in Bosnia be solved 
by Yugoslav nations themselves and primarily in a peaceful 
manner. The LUNSZ demands that NATO activity be ended "as it 
has been promised by NATO when the former Warsaw Pact ceased to 
exist." 

</TEXT>

