<H3> <TI>   Dlouhy Ready To Negotiate on U.S. Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dlouhy Ready To Negotiate on U.S. Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904132394 Prague CTK in English 1247 GMT 19 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague April 19 (CTK) -- The Czech Republic [CR] is 
prepared to enter negotiations on better access of Czech goods 
to the U.S. market and U.S. goods to the Czech market, Czech 
Trade and Industry Minister Vladimir Dlouhy said today. 
  Dlouhy was speaking to journalists after his meeting with 
U.S. presidential envoy and deputy chairman of a political 
guiding group for Central and Eastern Europe, Richard Schifter. 
  The United States is also to conduct negotiations with the 
other members of the Visegrad Four -- Slovakia, Poland and 
Hungary -- and Schifter will visit these countries within the 
next few days, Dlouhy said. 
  Dlouhy pointed out that the countries of the European Union 
account for between 55 and 60 percent of exports from the Czech 
Republic, while the United States represents only about one or 
two percent. Therefore it was a long-term priority of the Czech 
Republic to gain admission to the European Union, he explained. 
  Dlouhy announced there will be a White House sponsored 
conference of leading American and Central European companies in 
the summer. 

</TEXT>

