<F P=102>   AU1904193394 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1715 GMT 19 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 19/4/1994 -- Romanian and Dutch 
Prime Ministers Nicolae Vacaroiu and Ruud Lubbers assessed the 
necessary framework existed for fertile bilateral cooperation. 
It would be helped also by the Agreement on Mutual Guaranteeing 
and Protection of Investments, signed by the two premiers on 19 
April in Bucharest. 
  Other bilateral agreements will follow, including two 
documents on road and water transports, said Premier Vacaroiu 
during the news conference that followed the talks between the 
two heads of government. 
  Referring to Romania's current situation, the guest said 
that 
what was worst seemed to have been overcome. "We are interested 
in cooperation and expect many Dutch investors to come to 
Romania", Lubbers added. 
  Premier Vacaroiu stressed that the visit demonstrated the 
upward course of the bilateral relations. 
  Premier Lubbers told the same news conference about the 
Netherlands' initiative to back, through the PHARE [Economic 
Reconstruction Aid for Poland and Hungary] program, Romania's 
efforts to cut down power consumption and improve the technical 
performance in urban central heating. 

</TEXT>

