<H3> <TI>   Central European Presidents Meet in Lityomysl </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central European Presidents Meet in Lityomysl </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Weizsacker on `Problems of the Past' </H4>

<F P=102> AU1504201694 Prague CTK in English 1630 GMT 15 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1504201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Litomysl, East Bohemia, April 15 (CTK) -- German 
President Richard von Weizsacker today called for dialogue 
between the concerned groups to remove problems of the past 
which burden German-Czech relations. Speaking at a press 
conference after the first round of talks between seven Central 
European presidents here, Weizsacker said that the past was 
still markedly affecting the two countries' relations and that 
it was "important to free them of past errors which are still 
affecting them." 
  This should be done through dialogue "not only between 
governments, but also between representatives of the groups 
which themselves experienced these bad times," Weizsacker said. 
He stressed that not property questions, but "a moral and 
historical evaluation of the past," a " typical task" for the 
two countries' presidents, was of priority importance. 
  Weizsacker was probably hinting at the issue of the 2.5 
Sudeten Germans who were expelled from Czechoslovakia after 
World War Two and whose property was expropriated, and at the 
German occupation of the Czech Lands during the war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

