<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central European Presidents Meet in Lityomysl </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Walesa on `Special Formula' for Russia </H4>

<F P=102> AU1804083794 Prague CTK in English 2145 GMT 15 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1804083794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Litomysl, East Bohemia, April 15 (CTK) -- Polish 
President Lech Walesa, in his talks with President Vaclav Havel 
tonight, said he was afraid of a special formula for Russia 
within the Partnership for Peace plan, Pavel Seifter from 
Havel's office told journalists. 
  He added that Walesa said this "special formula" for Russia 
could be dangerous to Europe. Havel voiced a similar 
apprehension, though not so strong as Walesa, Seifter said. 
  Walesa said he was satisfied with today's meeting. Reacting 
to Hungarian President Arpad Goncz's invitation extended to the 
seven Central European presidents to come to a similar meeting 
to Hungary next year, Walesa said that he "will have" to invite 
the presidents to the next meeting. 

</TEXT>

