<H3> <TI>   Security Council Acknowledges Aid on Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Council Acknowledges Aid on Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904103594 Tirana ATA in English 0808 GMT 19 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 19 (ATA) -- Through a letter of April 
18, 1994, Ronaldo Sardenberg, chairman of the Security Council 
Committee created by the 724 Resolution on the former Yugoslavia 
(Serbia and Montenegro), expressed its thanks to the Albanian 
Government with regard to its stands towards violations of the 
embargo by other ships, which have been detained and 
investigated by Albanian authorities. 
  The committee expresses in particular its appreciation for 
the good cooperation of the Albanian Government with the embargo 
assistance mission in Albania. The letter says that the 
investigations of the Albanian Government into the case of the 
"Vela Luka" ship and other cases have been considered by the 
committee as ample facts proving the violation of the embargo by 
foreign ships. 
  The committee has been informed by Albanian authorities for 
the "Valio" ship with 1,200 tons of gasoline, which tried to 
enter Yugoslavia, thus violating the embargo. 

</TEXT>

