<H3> <TI>   Berov Working in Hospital; Health `Good' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berov Working in Hospital; Health `Good' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804114594 Sofia BTA in English 1056 GMT 18 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1804114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, April 18 (BTA) -- Prime Minister Lyuben 
Berov is working in the privacy of his hospital room at the 
Lozenets Hospital of the Military Medical Academy in Sofia, the 
government Press Office said today. "Prof. Berov is in a good 
state of health. His stomach complaint and the slight yellowing 
of his eyes have passed," says a communique issued today at noon 
by Dr. Todor Gerasimov, chief of the Lozenets Hospital. Berov's 
liver function is returning to normal, biochemical tests carried 
out in Bulgaria show. Blood serum has been sent to Germany to 
be tested for hepatitis type C but the results are not out yet. 
  A month ago Berov had a quadruple bypass operation from 
which 
he recuperated enough to attend a government meeting. Early 
last week he was hospitalized again as he developed the symptoms 
of an acute liver condition. The diagnosis has not been 
specified yet. Medics assume that Berov either had a passing 
mechanical obstruction of the bile ducts or suffered from a 
light form of viral hepatitis type C. 

</TEXT>

