<H3> <TI>   Dogan Wants To Discuss Cabinet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dogan Wants To Discuss Cabinet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804184494 Sofia BTA in English 1657 GMT 18 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1804184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, April 18 (BTA) -- The leader of the ethnic 
Turks' Movement for Rights and Freedoms (DPS) Ahmed Dogan asked 
for an appointment with Prime Minister Prof. Lyuben Berov. Mr. 
Dogan met today with Deputy Prime Minister Evgeni Matinchev, who 
is entitled to head the cabinet during the prime minister's 
absence through illness. 
  Ahmed Dogan wanted to know when he would be able to meet 
with 
the prime minister personally, Mr. Matinchev said after the 
meeting. He said that DPS had certain ideas about structural 
changes in Prof. Berov's Cabinet, (which was formed on the DPS's 
mandate). However, he declined to give details or comment. 
  "An overhaul of the cabinet would open new opportunities to 
the government, but its performance over the next three or four 
weeks will be of vital importance, for it will show whether we 
shall ask for such an overhaul," Mr. Dogan said after the 
meeting. He said that their ideas about structural changes in 
the cabinet were still at the probing stage. Mr. Dogan hopes to 
meet with Prof. Berov as soon as he is allowed by the doctors. 
Asked whether this will be the first appointment of the prime 
minister after his hospitalization, Mr. Dogan answered that he 
hoped so. 

</TEXT>

