<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   New TV Program Council Chairman Elected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New TV Program Council Chairman Elected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104091194 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1648 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104091194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 20 Apr--The Program Council of Polish 
Television S.A. [joint-stock company] was formed on 20 April. 
Jozef Zych, deputy Sejm speaker and Polish Peasant Party [PSL] 
deputy, was elected chairman of the council. Zbigniew Niezgoda, 
head of the Office of the Polish Television Board S.A., said 
that film director Krzysztof Zanussi and defense lawyer and 
scriptwriter Krzysztof Piesiewicz were elected deputy chairmen. 
  Other members of the program council are Maria 
Braun-Galkowska, Lublin Catholic University professor; Maciej 
Englert, film director; Ryszard Jarzembowski, the Democratic 
Left Alliance [SLD] senator; Krzysztof Krol, the Confederation 
for an Independent Poland deputy; Jacek Kurczewski, Warsaw 
University professor; Zdobyslaw Milewski, Democratic Union 
deputy; Jan Sek, PSL senator; Adam Struzik, PSL senator and 
senate speaker; Ryszard Ulicki, SLD deputy; Andrzej Urbanczyk, 
SLD deputy; Marek Wielgus, the Non-Party Bloc in Support of 
Reforms deputy; and Krzysztof Wolicki, journalist. 

</TEXT>

