<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy To Visit in Early May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy To Visit in Early May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004133094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1238 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 20 Apr (TANJUG) -- Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, 
president of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, has 
accepted an invitation from Mirko Jovic, president of the Serb 
National Renewal [SNO], to visit our country at the beginning of 
May, the SNO says in a statement issued today. The statement 
says that the visit will last three days and will take place 
within the framework of cooperation between the two parties and 
the talks on developing a "pan-Slav Christian union". 

</TEXT>

