<DOCNO> FBIS4-9102 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu077_y_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-077 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Vojvodina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Industrial Production Increases 39.8 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Industrial Production Increases 39.8 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004162194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1153 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004162194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Novi Sad, 20 Apr (TANJUG) -- Industrial 
production in Vojvodina increased by 39.8 percent in March 
compared to February this year. A further increase is expected 
in April, given that loans have been granted to revive 
production, Todor Balos, member of the Vojvodina Economic 
Chamber Board told TANJUG today. He said that industrial 
production in the first three months of this year was at a 
slightly lower level than in the same period last year, but the 
March results, which were better than in February, as well as 
the expected further increase in production, indicated that we 
are on the path of reviving production in line with the 
country's stabilization program. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

