<H3> <TI>   Situation in Gorazde -- 21 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Gorazde -- 21 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Missiles Reportedly From Montenegro </H4>

<F P=102> AU2104091594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2104091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enes Musovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Text] The chetniks have only stopped short of dropping an 
atom bomb on the residents of Gorazde. They are mercilessly 
killing the people with everything they have, destroying their 
houses. Yesterday afternoon, the chetniks wreaked havoc in 
Gorazde with aerosol surface-to-surface missiles PAB-275. 
Houses were destroyed as if made out of cards. The roofs of 
all buildings within a radius of 200 meters were blown off and 
the walls fractured. Dozens of people were killed and wounded. 
Owing to the constant fire by chetniks from the surrounding 
hills, the casualties have not yet been evacuated from these 
ruins. 
  According to reliable information, these missiles were 
launched from Pljevlje [in Montenegro, 60 km away]. This is yet 
another proof of the involvement by the so-called Yugoslavia in 
the aggression on Bosnia-Herzegovina. The crying and screaming 
of the seriously wounded were heard coming from these ruins 
throughout the night. 
  The Gorazde valley is a valley of pain, screaming, and 
horror. The constant deadly pounding by those who do not 
distinguish between killing people and drinking water last night 
killed Dr. Muhamed Pasic, who, despite a rain of sniper bullets, 
went to give medical help to the seriously wounded in the 1 May 
district. 
  This morning, the chetniks are continuing the realization of 
their bloody plan, wiping Gorazde from the face of the earth. 
The chetniks confirmed this morning that they only understand 
the language of force and that they are unable to live in peace. 
The inferno in Gorazde continues. Further human lives are 
being lost, so is the hope among the survivors that someone will 
finally demonstrate to the chetniks with force that the time of 
cavemen, barbarism, and unpunished crime has long gone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

