<H3> <TI>   Situation in Gorazde -- 21 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Gorazde -- 21 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    TANJUG: Muslims Resume Attacks </H4>

<F P=102> LD2104085894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0809 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, 21 Apr (TANJUG) -- This morning, the Muslim 
army resumed its heavy artillery and mortar attacks from the 
center of Gorazde on the Serbian army positions on the right 
bank of the Drina, the command of the Hercegovina corps of the 
Serbian Army has announced. Strong Muslim forces are in 
evidence near the town's bridges. Serbian military sources see 
this as a likely indication that the Muslims are preparing to 
destroy the bridges. Throughout yesterday afternoon NATO planes 
frequently flew over Serbian army positions at an altitude of 
over 3,000 meters. This provided the Muslims with an additional 
motive to intensify their combat activities. Yesterday the 
Muslims tried to use for propaganda purposes an incident in the 
chemical plant in Vitkovici, four kilometers south of Gorazde, 
to accuse the Serbs of using poison gases. 
  The Herzegovina corps command stresses that due to the low 
level of technological process in the plant there is a danger of 
a genuine ecological catastrophe throughout the Drina basin. 
Over the past 24 hours two Serbian fighters have been wounded 
on the Gorazde front. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

