<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croats Reportedly Repel Serbian Attacks on Brcko </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croats Reportedly Repel Serbian Attacks on Brcko </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004162994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Early this afternoon the defenders of the Croat 
Defense Council [HVO] and the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army repelled a 
number of furious Serbian attacks supported by over 1,500 
artillery shells on the Dubravice-Bodariste-Vranovaca defense 
line in the northeast section of the free territory of Brcko, 
the political department of the 108th HVO Infantry Brigade 
reports. 
  In the Bodariste area, the HVO defenders have destroyed one 
Serbian tank and disabled an estimated several dozen attackers, 
the 108th HVO Brigade reports. The defense lines remain 
unchanged. There have been no casualties among the fighters. 
One civilian has, however, been killed in an artillery attack 
on targets of the free territory behind the front line, the HVO 
reports. 
  Apart from this, some 50 shells, ranging from 20 to 203 mm 
caliber, land every hour on the free territory against the 
backdrop of constant Serbian infantry attacks on the lines of 
defense. In the north section of the battlefield the defenders 
of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army repelled an infantry attack on 
the Vitanovici and Bajici area last night. Seven Serbian tanks 
supported this attack. The defense lines remain unchanged. We 
do not know whether there were any casualties, the 108th HVO 
Infantry Brigade reports. 

</TEXT>

