<H3> <TI>   Croats Fire on Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croats Fire on Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004190794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1820 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Banja Luka, 20 Apr (TANJUG) -- A woman was injured 
in Brcko today when the regular army of the Republic of Croatia 
launched an attack from multiple rocket-launchers, the 
information service of the 1st Krajina Corps of the republic of 
Srpska army said in Banja Luka this evening. This was the 
second multiple rocket-launcher attack today and it was carried 
out at about 1600. Altogether six rockets were fired from 
positions on the left bank of the Sava river, i.e. from the 
territory of the Republic of Croatia, and both attacks were 
launched on civilian targets. In addition to multiple 
rocket-launcher attacks, Croatian artillery fired 16 shells on 
the [Bosnia] Serb villages of Krepsic and Loncari from positions 
near Zupanja and Bosnjaci, also from the territory of the 
Republic of Croatia. Nobody was wounded in the attack but 
considerable material damage was caused. 
  Republic of Srpska army units were forced to respond to the 
attacks. 
  All this confirms assumptions that an intensification of 
attacks can be expected, which is aimed at severing the corridor 
which links the republic of Serb Krajina and the republic of 
Srpska with the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

