<H3> <TI>   Army Destroys Serbian Tank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Destroys Serbian Tank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2004194994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2004194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hamiz Deronjic from Brcko] </F>
  [Excerpt] Another enemy tank -- the fourth one since the 
outset of the massive chetnik offensive -- has been destroyed on 
the Brcko front. After hours of shelling our positions this 
morning, the Serbian aggressor early this afternoon made yet 
another attempt to break through the defense lines with strong 
armored and mechanized forces. With heavy artillery support, 
the tank and infantry attack was carried out in two directions, 
toward Omerbegovaca-Vranovaca and Boderiste-Vranovaca. The 
fighters of the 108th Infantry Brigade and the 108th Motorized 
Brigade responded well to this attack. About a dozen chetniks 
were killed in infantry fighting and the fighters of the 108th 
Brigade fired a precise shot and destroyed a chetnik tank with 
the entire crew. 
  The fighters of the legendary 108th Motorized Brigade have 
asked us to say that this was their way of expressing their 
support for the defenders and citizens of Gorazde. They say: 
We cannot rout the chetniks around Gorazde but, for Gorazde, we 
will rout the chetniks here. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

