<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croats To Compromise on Silajdzic Presidency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croats To Compromise on Silajdzic Presidency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004170594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Members of the executive committee and chairmen of 
the municipal councils of the Croatian Democratic Union [HDZ] of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina have confirmed their support for full 
implementation of the Washington agreement. At their meeting in 
Mostar, they also discussed the political and security situation 
in Bosnia-Herzegovina and the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna. 
Zdenko Vranjes has filed this report: 
  [Vranjes] Addressing the members of the executive committee 
and the chairmen of the municipal committees of the HDZ in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, Kresimir Zubak, president of the 
presidential council of the Croat republic, said that a majority 
of the Croatian and Bosniak people want to implement the 
Washington agreement and the constitution of the federation. 
The minority of the Croatian nation which would like to 
obstruct the Washington agreement must be aware that it fulfills 
the interests of the entire Croatian nation both in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the Republic of Croatia. We must 
continue to stress that Bosnia-Herzegovina is our homeland in 
order to prevent anybody from making exclusive claims on it. 
  Zubak said that talks on the presidency of the federation in 
the interim period will be resumed with Bosniak representatives 
on Saturday. Under the constitution, the Croatian side wants to 
have their man as president in the interim stage. However, 
Zubak added, the Croatian side is prepared to accept a 
compromise if the Muslim side insists on a Muslim president of 
the federation and if Haris Silajdzic is nominated for this 
position. 

</TEXT>

