<H3> <TI>   Russian Ambassador Calls For Bosnian Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Ambassador Calls For Bosnian Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2004113794 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2004113794 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Russian Ambassador's First News </F>
Conference"] 
  [Text] At his first news conference, Russian Ambassador to 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
Yuriy Petrovich Trusin announced his country will open an 
embassy in Skopje at the beginning of May. The conference 
focused on Moscow's position on events in Bosnia. He described 
the situation there as dangerous. The Russian view, he said, is 
this conflict must be resolved through an equal cooperation 
between the United States, Russia, and the European Union, but 
under UN surveillance. Moscow insists that the parties in the 
war declare an immediate cease-fire and sit down at the 
negotiating table. Trusin said Russia also demands and urgent 
lifting of the sanctions against Yugoslavia. In regard to 
yesterday's statement by [Deputy Foreign Minister] Churkin that 
Russia ought to break negotiations with Bosnian Serbs, because 
of their failure to keep promises, Trusin said it was an 
emotional remark and added his country's attitude toward the 
Bosnian crisis remains unchanged. 

</TEXT>

