<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "President Iliescu Wants To Clarify </F>
Ex-King's Position"] 
  [Text] "The ex-king must issue a clear statement to 
receive an entry visa for Romania," President Ion Iliescu has 
said in an answer to an AFP reporter's question. The Romanian 
Government had an open attitude in 1992, when King Mihai I was 
in Romania; in autumn 1993 he was asked to adopt a clear 
position toward the rules of the Romanian Constitution. "I do 
not want to take similar measures to those taken throughout 
history by France, Italy, or Greece (in connection with former 
monarchs and their direct descendants). Therefore, we want to 
have a clear statement from him," said President Iliescu, who 
avoided giving a clear answer to the question: "Will King Mihai 
be granted an entry visa to Romania?" 

</TEXT>

