<F P=102>   AU2004203194 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2004203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have just received a report from the spokesman 
of the Albanian Foreign Ministry: 
  Deputy Foreign Minister Arian Starova, at a meeting today, 
informed Greek Ambassador in Tirana Tsalikis that the Albanian 
side welcomes the Greek proposal for a meeting at the foreign 
minister level in Zurich, Switzerland on 3 May. 
  By responding in this way, Albania is showing that it 
respects the choice of dialogue and is committed to finding ways 
to normalize relations with Greece. 
  While this meeting was held in Tirana, it has been learned 
that the Greek Foreign Ministry summoned Albanian Ambassador 
Hysen Cabej to an urgent meeting at the Greek Foreign Ministry 
and notified him that the diplomatic staff should be reduced 
from five diplomats to four. 
  Such a fact, which runs counter to statements by Greek 
Government officials on finding a way to dialogue and 
cooperation, cannot but surprise anyone. After this, it is 
somewhat difficult to understand the messages coming from Athens. 

</TEXT>

