  [Text] Political and diplomatic figures continue to arrive 
in Bucharest for tomorrow's Crans Montana Forum opening. Two 
prominent figures arrived about an hour ago: Catherine 
Lalumiere, acting secretary general of the Council of Europe 
[CE], who was welcomed at Otopeni International Airport by 
Ambassador Virgil Constantinescu, general director at the 
Romanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and Georg Reisch, general 
secretary of the European Free Trade Association [EFTA]. 
According to the schedule, Lalumiere will chair, together with 
President Ion Iliescu and Forum Foundation President Jean Paul 
Carteron, the inaugural session of the Crans Montana Forum in 
Bucharest on 21 April. 
  Upon his arrival at Otopeni Airport Reisch made the 
following 
statement to our radio station: 
  [Begin Reisch recording, in English with superimposed 
translation into Romanian] I am very glad to be here again as 
the head of EFTA. We want to have close ties with Romania. We 
have an accord on free trade exchanges and I am looking forward 
not only to presiding over a Forum session on the importance of 
free trade for international security, but also to meeting with 
Romanian officials to discuss details on the cooperation between 
Romania and EFTA. [end recording] 
  We remind you that Otar Patsatsia, prime minister of the 
Republic of Georgia, also arrived in Bucharest this evening. 
According to our correspondent Nicu Popescu, the following 
guests are also expected to arrive tonight: Mechyslaw Hryb, 
chairman of the Supreme Council of Belarus, and Shim'on Peres, 
