<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Chief Halts `Sign of Thought' Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Chief Halts `Sign of Thought' Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004104694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0900 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The deputy chairman of Hungarian Radio [Laszlo 
Csucs] has terminated the program "Sign of Thought." According 
to a report by PESTI HIRLAP, Laszlo Csucs explained his decision 
by stating that the editors of the Sunday cultural program -- 
Gabor Ocsovai, Miklos Gyoerffy, and Julia Varadi -- have been 
producing programs which were biased and have incited passions. 
  The deputy chairman expressed the view that the producers of 
the last edition did not adhere to even the most elementary 
ethical requirements. In Laszlo Csucs's judgment, further 
experimentation would be an abuse of the patience of the 
audience, and although the radio's cultural weekly was still 
needed, it would be produced not by the current staff and 
probably not under its current name. 

</TEXT>

