<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Adopts Presidential Veto on Electoral Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sejm Adopts Presidential Veto on Electoral Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104083894 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
0800 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Sejm has adopted a presidential veto against the 
parish councils' electoral law. The president refused to sign 
the law on the ground that its rules banning the election 
campaign in churches had violated the principles of the 
democratic state of law, equality before the law, and the 
separation of church and state. 
  The president also considers lowering a threshold for 
proportional representation as leading to the politicizing of 
the local self-government elections. 

</TEXT>

