<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation in Gorazde -- 21 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Gorazde -- 21 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serbs Closing on Town </H4>

<F P=102> LD2104090094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
0800 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The tragedy of Gorazde goes on. Thousands of shells 
have been destroying the center of the town while from the 
surrounding hills the chetniks are using their snipers and 
anti-aircraft weapons to monitor every movement in the town. No 
one can tell how many casualties there has been in the town. 
From all directions tanks are closing on the town center. 
According to as yet unconfirmed reports reaching the UN 
Protection Force [UNPROFOR] headquarters in Zagreb, Serb tanks 
are moving in the direction of part of the town which contains a 
munitions factory currently in Muslim hands. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-9148 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu077_i_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-077 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation in Gorazde -- Apr 20 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Gorazde -- Apr 20 </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Shelling Kills Captured Serbs </H4>

<F P=102> AU2004154094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1500 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2004154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mustafa Kurtovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Excerpts] The latest information from the outskirts, with 
which contact was lost, is that the situation in Vitkovici is 
dramatic. Yesterday alone, 11 civilians, six of them children 
under 10, were seriously wounded. They were wounded in attacks 
by portable rocket launchers and tanks from (Dilje) hill. These 
people cannot be helped, as the road to Vitkovici is completely 
cut off. They cannot be brought to the hospital or the medical 
center. The situation in the city center resembles the worst 
scene from a horror film. [passage omitted] 
  We have also just received information from the official 
bodies that Maljutka guided missiles have hit the prison camp 
with 22 captured members of the fascist army. Six captured 
chetniks have been killed and eight seriously wounded in this 
barbaric attack. We have also received information from the 
clinic that 19 of our citizens have been wounded by sniper fire 
so far. Two of them, Milinkovic Dusan and his wife, have died, 
despite being given urgent aid. 

</TEXT>

