<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: Army Must Adapt to NATO Standards </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official: Army Must Adapt to NATO Standards </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104120894 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1121 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104120894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 21 Apr--According to First Deputy Defense 
Minister Jerzy Milewski, the Polish Army must adapt itself to 
joint actions with the NATO states' armies. When Poland becomes 
a member of NATO, its entire Army or a part of it may find 
itself under foreign command, Milewski said today during a 
meeting with journalists in Warsaw on Poland's defense policy. 
  Milewski and other high-ranking representatives of the 
National Defense Ministry emphasized that Poland will not be 
able to defend itself in anything greater than a local conflict. 
According to them, there is no great threat of an outbreak of a 
global conflict or a great conventional war in Europe today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

