  [Text] Ibrahim Rugova, president of the republic of 
Kosova, is holding meetings with foreign diplomats. Mehmet 
Haziri: 
  [Haziri] The Kosova Information Center reports that today, 
President Ibrahim Rugova received three countries' CSCE 
representatives -- (Laura Mehatian), charge d'affaires at the 
Italian Embassy; (Goran Jacobson) and (Thorsten Petren), charge 
d'affaires at the Swedish Embassy; as well as (Andreas Vinzel), 
charge d'affaires at the Hungarian Embassy in Belgrade. 
President Rugova informed the CSCE diplomats of recent 
developments and the grave situation in Kosova. Also, in a 
meeting with Mrs. (Ann Brulant), charge d'affaires of the 
Norwegian Embassy in Belgrade, and (Siri Ovre), they talked 
about the present situation in Kosova and recent developments in 
the region. 
  In both of these meetings, President Rugova spoke of the 
continuing aggravation of the situation in Kosova due to the 
constant increase in Serbian repression and violence against the 
Albanian population. The CSCE diplomats and the Norwegians 
stayed in Kosova to complete their fact-finding mission on the 
present trends and efforts of Albanian political parties and 
individuals in attempting to resolve all problems peacefully and 
through dialogue. 

