<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Professionalization of Army Proceeding </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Professionalization of Army Proceeding </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2004202594 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 16 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2004202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Professionalization Is Beginning"] </F>
  [Text] Presov--Defense Minister Pavol Kanis visited the 
14th Mechanized Division in Presov yesterday. He met with its 
commander, Colonel Jan Cmilansky, and with the Division's corps 
of commanders. During their discussion, he briefed them on the 
current situation in the Slovak Army. The defense minister 
said, among other things, that the number of personnel in our 
Army should be reduced to 46,667 by November 1995, in accordance 
with the Vienna Agreements. "For this reason, procedures have 
to be adopted to ensure that the state's defense capability is 
not weakened. This is also necessary because the Army has 
already been reduced by 32 percent due to its division following 
the breakup of Czechoslovakia." At a meeting with reporters, 
Kanis said, in connection with the Army's professionalization, 
that "preparations are already under way in this regard. 
Professionalization is proceeding in the two mechanized 
battalions in Bratislava, and it will be enough to 
professionalize 390 noncommissioned officer posts in order to 
make a significant positive change." 

</TEXT>

