<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unemployment Falls Slightly in March </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unemployment Falls Slightly in March </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204075094 Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Slovak 19 Apr 
94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "A Slight Decline in Unemployment"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--Some 370,493 job seekers, of whom 
98,666 were receiving social security, were registered at labor 
offices in Slovakia at the end of March. According to a report 
from the Ministry of Labor, Social Affairs, and the Family, the 
unemployment level in March fell from 14.76 to 14.54 percent. 
  The highest unemployment level, 26.3 percent, is in the 
Rimavska Sobota District; it is followed by the Spisska Nova Ves 
and Vranov nad Toplou Districts. The lowest unemployment level 
is still being recorded in the Bratislava-City (4.27 percent), 
Trencin, and Kosice-City Districts. 
  The number of vacancies increased in March, but, despite 
this, there are 40 job seekers per vacancy. 

</TEXT>

