<H3> <TI>   Continued Fighting Reported in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Continued Fighting Reported in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Tank Attacks Reported </H4>

<F P=102> AU2204084494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fahrudin Becic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Text] This morning's attacks, which started at 0540, 
intensified at about 0800. The entire city is again targeted, 
but the area around the hospital and the hospital itself, half 
of which is almost completely demolished, are exposed to the 
heaviest attacks. It is impossible to provide aid to the 
wounded, what with the constant attacks with tanks and rockets 
and the lack of all kinds of medicine and sanitary material. 
The lives of the wounded and the medical staff are in constant 
danger. 
  The tanks on the right side of the Drina River are only 
several hundred meters from the hospital. At 0845 they moved a 
bit closer to the center of the city, demolishing it house by 
house on their way. At 0910 the chetniks opened heavy small 
arms fire from all their positions on the right bank. However, 
the front lines have not moved and the entire city is still 
under the control of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army. 
  The chetniks are attacking fiercely on the left bank. The 
district of (Obarac) is under attack, while tanks have been 
demolishing the 1 May Street from the direction of the city 
stadium. The attacks are also intensifying at the defense line 
toward [word indistinct], where the aggressor has been bringing 
reinforcements. [Word indistinct] missiles have been fired from 
Ustipraca at the eastern sector, and from (?Stubiste) at the 
southern sector. 

</TEXT>

