  [Excerpt] Cajnice, 22 Apr (TANJUG) -- The Muslim military 
and civil leadership from Gorazde has rejected the Serbian 
side's offer whereby all combat activities would be halted and 
the warring parties would be separated by a demarcation line 
running along the Drina, TANJUG reporters have learned from 
Serbian military sources. The Serbian side's proposition was 
rejected late last night. Heavy fire from all weaponry was 
opened on Serbian positions shortly afterward. Fighting resumed 
this morning along the demarcation lines on the left and the 
right banks of the Drina, the Herzegovina Corps [of the Bosnian 
Serb army] reports. It adds that one Serbian fighter was killed 
and several were wounded in last night's clashes. [passage 
omitted] 

