<DOCNO> FBIS4-9191 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu078_i_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-078 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Give Withdrawal Ultimatum to Army in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Give Withdrawal Ultimatum to Army in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104171494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Serbian aggressor forces have issued an 
ultimatum to the forces of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army in 
Gorazde, demanding that they withdraw completely from the right 
bank of the River Drina. They can remain on the left bank only 
in the 3-km circle around the town center. This has been 
announced from the Embassy of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
in Zagreb. 

</TEXT>

