<H3> <TI>   Silajdzic Views Ultimatum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Silajdzic Views Ultimatum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2104181694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2104181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In light of the ultimatum that the chetniks have 
issued to the defenders and the residents of Gorazde, 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic gave the 
following statement: 
  [Begin Silajdzic recording] An hour ago, we were informed 
that the representatives of the aggressor (?had handed) an 
ultimatum to our forces in Gorazde, demanding that our forces 
withdraw completely from the right bank of the Drina River, from 
Gorazde, and from the left bank (?with the exception of the 
very) center, where [words indistinct]. 
  If our forces do not do this today by [word indistinct] 
(?afternoon) the representatives of the aggressor threaten to 
destroy everything in Gorazde, including [words indistinct]. 
  Therefore, instead of the NATO ultimatum we have the 
aggressor's ultimatum. Naturally, we have informed all the 
relevant factors about this, including [UN envoy] Mr. Akashi, 
[UN Protection Force] General Rose, Washington, and naturally, 
we have sent a letter to the chairman of the UN Security 
Council, demanding urgent actions to prevent a new catastrophe 
in Gorazde. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

