<H3> <TI>   UNPROFOR Orders Convoy To Return to Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNPROFOR Orders Convoy To Return to Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204124594 Paris AFP in English 1229 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2204124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 22 (AFP) -- United Nations 
Protection Force [UNPROFOR] commander General Michael Rose 
ordered a UN convoy heading for the eastern Bosnian town of 
Gorazde to return to Sarajevo Friday [22 April], an UNPROFOR 
spokesman said. The order to return, issued around 1:30 p.m. 
(1130 GMT), was made "for tactical and political reasons," 
spokesman Rob Annink said. The convoy had been blocked by Serb 
women protesters. 

</TEXT>

