<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Reportedly Shelling Bihac From Krajina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Reportedly Shelling Bihac From Krajina </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204092394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] Karadzic's fascists are continuing with their 
attacks on the Bihac region, particularly on Buzim and the 
surrounding area, and the free Bosanska Krupa territory. The 
shelling of residential areas and the defense lines has 
continued throughout the night and this morning, particularly 
from the territory of the Republic of Croatia, that is, from the 
so-called Serbian autonomous region of Krajina. These areas 
have been attacked from the back, while the local rebels and 
traitors have been shelling them sporadically from their 
strongholds in Golubovici and (?Travnica). During the night 
they fired at the Cazin outskirts, trying to instigate infantry 
clashes. Their main target is still the [word indistinct] 
production facilities. 
  On the Bihac part of the front, in the operative zones of 
the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 5th Corps and the Croatian Defense 
Council [HVO], and on the Grmusko-Srbljanski Plateau, the 
chetniks have been behaving in their usual manner, which means 
unselectively shelling the defense lines, firing with 
antiaircraft weapons and small arms, and infiltrating smaller 
sabotage groups that keep trying to penetrate well inside our 
territory. The chetniks have continued to bring in equipment 
from the occupied Croatian territory, deploying it in the hills 
surrounding the Bihac commune. They are also carrying out 
engineering work and digging in. 

</TEXT>

