<H3> <TI>   Serbs Offer to Trade French Hostages for Prisoners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Offer to Trade French Hostages for Prisoners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204051694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204051694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The French Humanitarian organization (?Premiere) 
[word indistinct] has reported that Karadzic's Serbs have 
offered to exchange 11 humanitarian workers from this 
organization, whom they have held prisoner for two weeks, for 11 
Serbian prisoners in Sarajevo. The association received this 
proposal in a letter from Dragan Kalinic, so-called health 
minister of the Bosnian Serbs. Kalinic wrote that among the 11 
imprisoned Serbs are five doctors and two nurses, and added that 
the French humanitarians were caught when they tried to deliver 
non-humanitarian aid to the Muslims. The French Ambassador to 
Bosnia-Herzegovina informed the organization that the 11 
humanitarian volunteers could be tried soon. 

</TEXT>

