<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK Assembly Endorses New Government Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RSK Assembly Endorses New Government Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104170994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1548 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 21 Apr (TANJUG) -- At a session in Knin this 
afternoon, deputies of the republic of Serb Krajina [RSK] 
assembly elected a government of national unity proposed by 
Borislav Mikelic. Fifty deputies voted in favor of the 
government, 14 were against, and nine abstained. The election of 
the government was preceded by a brief discussion during which 
the deputies gave overall support to the program and composition 
of the government. 
  There will be no representatives of the Serbian Radical 
Party 
in Mikelic's cabinet, but Mikelic himself said that a 
reconstruction of the government could be expected very soon 
because of the construction of new ministries. Mikelic added 
that the first government session will be held tomorrow to put 
the new program into action. 
  RSK President Martic told TANJUG that the election of the 
new 
government greatly contributes to the stabilization of internal 
affairs in Krajina. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

