<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Martic, Mikelic Comment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Martic, Mikelic Comment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2104201094 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1730 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2104201094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statements by Milan Martic, president of the republic of </F>
Serbian Krajina, and Borislav Mikelic, prime minister of the 
republic of Serbian Krajina, in Knin on 21 April -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Martic] I am (?firmly) convinced that the 
government will be capable of rising to the task before it. It 
is composed of all parties -- only the Radicals did not join 
owing to some reason of theirs, but I do not wish to elaborate 
-- however, regardless of the parties in question, and judging 
by the individuals, I believe that the government is quite a 
good one and that the people and the parliament will very soon 
be able to assess the work of this government. Personally, I 
think that it [the government] will be a good one. 
  [Mikelic] I think that we are now a entering a phase in the 
peace process that has been signed, and that means that we need 
to make this connection selectively, from people who are going 
from their positions toward production [sentence as heard]. On 
the other hand, we must see which companies we will tackle 
first, in individual municipalities where they have a 
perspective; at the same time we need to stop certain declines, 
particularly in areas where state-owned property suffered 
significant damage [sentence as heard]. I am extremely glad 
that this program was given general support today. I am also 
glad that the Serbian Democratic Party [SDS], and its president, 
Milan Babic, have managed to rise above the parliamentary 
coalition that used to exist in the assembly, and that he 
[Babic] has now truly placed the national interest of the 
Serbian people at the forefront. I am glad that he came alone 
to this post of foreign minister. The remaining ministers will 
surely be capable of shouldering the burden I mentioned earlier 
in my address. 

</TEXT>

