<H3> <TI>   New Government Dominated by SDS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Government Dominated by SDS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104200294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1639 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Knin, 21 Apr (TANJUG) -- The Serb Democratic 
Party [SDS] of Krajina has won the largest number of portfolios 
in the republic of Serb Krajina government. This party has won 
seven ministerial posts, while its leader, Milan Babic, has been 
appointed foreign affairs minister. 
  The Serb Democratic Party of Serbian Lands has won two 
portfolios while the socialists and the social democrats have 
won one portfolio each. 
  Six ministries, including the Ministries of Defense, 
Internal 
Affairs, and Finance will be headed by nonparty personalities. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

