<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Continued Fighting Reported in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Continued Fighting Reported in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serbian Tank Hits Refugees </H4>

<F P=102> AU2204105394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enes Musovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The chetniks have been firing 
selectively at civilian targets this morning. The refugee 
center has been hit. At about 1030 a tank caused bloody havoc 
in the Red Cross refugee center, where the old and the weak have 
been housed. Since this facility is still under constant 
chetnik artillery fire, the total number of casualties is still 
unknown. So far the bodies of four killed, and five wounded old 
folk have been dragged out. The evacuation of others is still 
under way. We have just received information that a tank shell 
in the center of Gorazde has killed one person, and wounded six 
others. This is just one illustration of the hell in Gorazde, 
just one example of the suffering of these people. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

