<F P=100> Bulgaria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meet With Daskalov, Matinchev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meet With Daskalov, Matinchev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2004184894 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2004184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Vanya Manolova] </F>
  [Text] Today Bulgarian Foreign Ministry Stanislav Daskalov 
and Peter Kooijmans, foreign minister of the Netherlands, who is 
visiting our country, signed a joint political declaration of 
the two countries' Foreign Ministries. According to Mr. 
Daskalov, the document specifies the main directions for 
bilateral cooperation, but the important thing is that these are 
refracted through the prism of our common aims to integrate us 
in the European and Euro- Atlantic structures. 
  Prior to this, Acting Prime Minister Evgeni Matinchev talked 
for almost two hours with Netherlands Prime Minister Ruud 
Lubbers and Foreign Minister Peter Kooijmans. During the 
meeting they discussed the difficulties of the transition and 
the possibilities for stimulating our bilateral relations, 
especially in the sphere of investments and cooperation in 
providing financial credits. 
  Through its representatives, the Netherlands assured us that 
in the near future it will ratify the interim trade agreement 
between Bulgaria and the European Union. The guests expressed 
the Netherlands' readiness to invest in our transportation 
projects, including the new Danube bridge. 

</TEXT>

