<H4>    Israel's Peres on Talks With Arafat </H4>

<F P=102> AU2104164694 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1216 GMT 21 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2104164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 21/4/1994 -- Israel's Minister 
of Foreign Affairs Shim'on Peres said he would continue Thursday 
[22 April] in Bucharest the talks with Yasir 'Arafat. A first 
round of talks took place last night until 0300 in the morning. 
  Shim'on Peres said that during the talks the sides are 
trying 
to assess the latest progress made in the Israeli-Palestinian 
negotiations. We feel we are very close to a conclusion and we 
want to translate the conclusions of the negotiations into the 
practical achievement of a new reality in the Middle East, 
Shim'on Peres said, adding that when the few problems still 
awaiting negotiation in Cairo are settled, a conclusion of the 
negotiations would be sought. 

</TEXT>

