<H4>    Melescanu Meets Belarus' Hryb </H4>

<F P=102> AU2104173694 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1218 GMT 21 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2104173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 21/4/1994 -- "Such actions are 
welcome for they occasion, through interviews and talks, an 
extensive exchange of opinions on current issues confronting our 
countries, especially regarding the process of transition to 
market economy," is the opinion of Mechyslaw Hryb, president of 
the Supreme Soviet of the Belarus Republic. 
  "I view this meeting as a beneficial one, proving Romania's 
wise policy towards openness. It will undoubtedly yield best 
results for expanding Romania's cooperation ties with other 
countries, especially economic ones. Romania has overcome the 
stage of expectations. What we have done here by organizing the 
Crans Montana Forum comes to prove Romania's real potential. We 
are seeking for an image much closer to the real one that would 
open new ways for our country. We are convinced that the Crans 
Montana Forum would reflect Romania's real potential which could 
attract foreign investors to our country," stated Romanian 
Foreign Minister Teodor Melescanu. 

</TEXT>

