<H3> <TI>   Crans Montana Forum -- Meetings, Highlights </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crans Montana Forum -- Meetings, Highlights </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Iliescu Answers Questions </H4>

<F P=102> AU2104164494 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1227 GMT 21 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2104164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 21/4/1994 -- Upon arrival in the 
Parliament Palace, Romania's President Ion Iliescu, surrounded 
by the press, was the target of a salvo of questions, starting 
from his always congenial mood, and the impressions about 
Placido Domingo's concert, and to the Crans Montana Forum 
conference topics. 
  The Romanian president found Domingo's concert "a good 
overture to this conference," and said he hoped the presence at 
the conference of the Israeli foreign minister and the PLO 
leader is a "good omen," showing optimism about the possibility 
of direct contacts these days in Bucharest. 
  Challenged by a journalist with the supposition that an 
agreement might be signed, the president said: "I do not know if 
the stage of signing an agreement will be reached, because 
negotiations are in progress. They will be coming with fresh 
information from the negotiations under way in Cairo, but we do 
hope that their meeting in Bucharest marks a positive step, 
stimulative for the ongoing of the negotiations." 
  President Iliescu also expressed the hope that the 
conference 
might contribute to the settlement of the Yugoslav crisis and to 
stopping the conflict in that area. 

</TEXT>

