<H4>    PLO Group Meets PSM Officials </H4>

<F P=102> AU2104164194 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1547 GMT 21 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2104164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 21/4/1994 -- A delegation of 
the Socialist Party of Labor of Romania [PSM], headed by 
President Ilie Verdet, met on 20 April evening with a delegation 
of the Palestine Liberation Organization, headed by Yasir 
'Arafat, PLO Executive Committee president, now in Romania for 
the Crans Montana forum proceedings. 
  The Palestinian party noted during the talks the traditional 
relations between Romanians and Palestinians, the fact that the 
Palestinian movement has always enjoyed full support, as 
regarded the right to self-determination of the Palestinian 
people and the negotiated settlement of the issue. 
  President Yasir 'Arafat said he felt encouraged by that 
meeting with the Romanian socialists. 
  The Socialist Party of Labor's leadership emphasized the 
possibility of expanding the relations between the two parties 
on multiple planes and the economic relations as well, to the 
benefit of the Romanian and Palestinian peoples. 

</TEXT>

