<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   People's Assembly Ratifies `Partnership' Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    People's Assembly Ratifies `Partnership' Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2104173194 Tirana ATA in English 1012 GMT 21 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2104173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 21 (ATA) -- On April 20, the People's 
Assembly ratified the document of Partnership for Peace [PFP] 
between Albania and NATO. The document between Albania and NATO 
was signed on February 23, 1994 in the NATO headquarters by the 
President of the Republic Sali Berisha. 
  According to the agreement, Albania will cooperate with NATO 
in questions of defence planning and budget, security and 
democratic control of the armed forces, in the capacities and 
readiness to contribute to the UN or CSCE operations, in 
training and manoeuvres for peace-keeping, search-saving, and 
humanitarian operations, as well as in the development of forces 
to enable them to operate with those of the NATO countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

