<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana April 20 (ATA) -- On April 20 Albanian 
ambassador in Athens, Hysen Cabej, was called to the Greek 
Foreign Ministry by the vice director of Balkan political 
department, Mr.Ralis, who presented the Greek request that the 
Albanian diplomatic staff be reduced by one more person. The 
present staff of the Albanian Embassy in Athens is composed of 
five diplomats. 
  Strangely enough, this fact runs counter to the statements 
uttered by the Greek government members themselves on finding a 
way to dialogue and cooperation. As a result, the message from 
Athens is difficult to be understood, says a statement of the 
spokesman of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Albania 
regarding this event. 

