<F P=103> AU2104084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 20 (ATA) -- The Ministry of the 
Public Order reported recently that several people have been 
detained for keeping arms without permission and criminal acts. 
The detention are in conformity with the law. 
  During the sudden controls the police organs have detained 
citizens from Vlore, Pogradeci, Delvina, Gjirokaster (south of 
Albania), Shkoder, Hasi, Bulqiza (north) and from Tirana 
(central Albania). The police has taken from them tommy guns, 
pistols, knives and munitions. 
  Besides the arms, the police has also confiscated a lot of 
anticonstitutional documents which proves the expansionist and 
annexionist Greek intentions toward Albania and the Albanian 
territories, as well as the flagrant Greek endeavour to make 
Greek the southern part of Albania. [sentence as received] 

</TEXT>

