<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   CSCE Envoy Hears Views on FYROM </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSCE Envoy Hears Views on FYROM </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2104184494 Tirana ATA in English 0806 GMT 21 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2104184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 21 (ATA) -- In the course of his 
visit to Albania, Norman Anderson, the chairman of CSCE mission 
in Skopje, met the Albanian President Sali Berisha, Deputy 
Foreign Minister Arjan Starova, public order and transport 
ministers, Mr. Musaraj and Mr. Bitincka respectively, on April 
20. In these meetings Mr. Anderson was interested in knowing 
Albanian views in reference to the Albanian-Macedonian 
relationship in general. 
  They focused mainly in the situation of Albanians in the 
Macedonian Republic [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM]. They pointed out in the meetings that Albania will 
continue to demand the respectability of the rights of Albanian 
people in Macedonia and wherever they are, which constitutes one 
of the priorities of Albanian foreign policy. The 
respectability of the Albanian rights constitutes an important 
element of stability in the whole region. 
  Firstly, in this framework Albania is interested in 
achievement in conformity to the international laws as soon as 
possible of the population census and the demands of the 
Albanians should be taken seriously by the census law. 
  At the same time was stressed the good will of the Albanian 
side to offer its territorial advantages for the passing of 
goods, because Macedonia suffers from Greek embargo. Not only 
for this reason but also foreseeing the future development of 
economical and commercial relationship with Macedonia, Albanian 
authorities pointed out the readiness for the further 
intensification of the relations, making concrete proposals to 
specific fields. 

</TEXT>

