<H3> <TI>   Socialist Ideas on Possible Coalition Partners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Socialist Ideas on Possible Coalition Partners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2104171694 Budapest MTI in English 1516 GMT 21 Apr 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2104171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 21 April (MTI) -- "If elected, the 
Socialists would choose the Alliance of Free Democrats and the 
Federation of Young Democrats as partners for coalition talks," 
Hungarian Socialist Party [MSZP] acting deputy chairman Imre 
Szekeres said in response to a reporter's question in Budapest 
on Thursday [21 April]. 
  "Only after knowing the election results can the MSZP think 
about (always assuming it is even in a position to) with whom to 
form a coalition," he added and cited four criteria for such a 
decision: Compatibility of party programs and an agreement on 
concrete government tasks for the first six months; consensus on 
the new government's composition and style; agreement to 
conclude a social pact; and partners' ability to create a 
constructive relationship with the opposition. 

</TEXT>

