<H3> <TI>   Walesa Denies Szczecin Visit Begins Campaign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa Denies Szczecin Visit Begins Campaign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204133294 Warsaw PAP in English 1159 GMT 22 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2204133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Szczecin, April 22 -- President Lech Walesa paying a 
several-hour visit to Szczecin said that this visit is not the 
start of his election campaign but a "wise campaign of balance." 
  Asked if he intends to run for presidency if the Non-Party 
Reform Bloc (BBWR) wins the June 19 local elections, the 
president replied: "There are still the parliamentary 
elections," and explained that he would have to have "executive 
capabilities" to implement his programme. 
  Following a meeting with supporters and members of the BBWR, 
the president met with the Szczecin-Kamien metropolitan, 
Archbishop Marian Przykucki. 
  Next the president left for a local military unit for a 
meeting with officers and representatives of police, border 
guards and fire fighters. 

</TEXT>

