<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Crans Montana Forum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Crans Montana Forum </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Peres Meeting With Velayati Denied </H4>

<F P=102> TA2204193494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 22 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2204193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres, on a visit to 
Bucharest, said he will arrive in Cairo in the next few days, 
where he might meet with PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat. Peres told 
reporters he hoped the Gaza and Jericho autonomy negotiations 
with the Palestinians will end within a week. Peres also said 
he will come to Cairo on 2 May again to participate in the 
autonomy's donors conference. 
  Today Peres held meetings in Bucharest with the presidents 
of 
Lithuania and Cyprus, Romania's prime minister and its 
parliament speaker. Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas 
said his country will open an embassy in Israel in the near 
future. 
  Sources in Peres' entourage denied rumors according to which 
Minister Peres will hold a meeting with Iranian Foreign Minister 
'Ali Akbar Velayati, who is scheduled to participate in the 
economic conference in Bucharest tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

